text: Bazita Peak TV Tower is a broadcasting tower in Zalaegerszeg, Hungary. The TV tower has a antenna on the top and an observation level up the structure. The Alps can be seen from the observation deck. It was built in 1975. == Other websites == *Offiicial web page *Kiskutas tourist information Category:Towers in Europe Category:Buildings and structures in Hungary Category:Zala County
